rebuild binaries, introduce node version compatibility.
improve error management to support RAISEERROR(); RAISERROR(); ...
add a test for this in edge-cases.ts

rebuild binaries, introduce node version compatibility.
improve error management to support RAISEERROR(); RAISERROR(); ...
add a test for this in edge-cases.ts

cancel a running query either via removing it from the work queue or by submitting to the C++ to cancel on sql server itself. Note this is a substantial update, and warrants careful testing before replacing the 0.2.x with the new 0.3.1 version including this functionality.
also add a new event 'submitted' which is raised when the query is actually sent to the C++ driver and on its way to SQL server.
candidate versions of binaries which now include the cancel query.
add back demo code - event demo now includes submitted event which is raised when the query is handed over to the c++.

running query in polling mode required for cancel support does impact performance in particular for a stream of fast small queries that do not need to be cancelled. Introduce a statement query poll mode which must be set on query object to support cancel so by default the query is still submitted blocked in the c++ worker thread. This means by default performance and behaviour is as before, but can set a statement to polling mode thus allowing a cancel to be submitted.
